"{\"uid\": \"oann.com-newsroom-olympics-opening-ceremony-features-drag-queens-mocking-biblical-last-supper-scene\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"OAN StaffJames Meyers4:06 PM - Friday, July 26, 2024  The opening ceremony of the 2024 Summer Olympics in Paris, France, turned heads while prompting backlash from some faith-based viewers.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 189, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 106, \"end\": 111, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999876145013, \"rank\": 1.2385387119864336e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 113, \"end\": 119, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.9998054997849004, \"rank\": 0.0001916191393703741, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The intro featured an eccentric performance that depicted a drag queen dressed as a blue smurf alongside other drag performers dancing on a runway, striving to build up excitement for the opening games.\", \"from\": 191, \"to\": 393, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Actual opening ceremony of the Olympics.This is not parody.RIP Olympics.pic.twitter.com/5gk1yObldB  More from the ritual known as the Olympics opening ceremony.A decapitated head (Marie Antoinette) singing.pic.twitter.com/5pR1YY85H9  The ceremony also included a \\\"headless Marie Antoinette,\\\" the last queen consort of France prior to the French Revolution who was married to King Louis XVI.\", \"from\": 395, \"to\": 785, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 575, \"end\": 591, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.981056284000709e-30, \"text\": \"Marie Antoinette\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\"}, {\"begin\": 668, \"end\": 684, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.981056284000709e-30, \"text\": \"Marie Antoinette\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\"}, {\"begin\": 713, \"end\": 719, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.9998054997849004, \"rank\": 0.0001916191393703741, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 775, \"end\": 784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_XVI\", \"score\": 0.999999996284032, \"rank\": 3.7153876860573484e-09, \"text\": \"Louis XVI\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_XVI\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_XVI\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Antoinette was found guilty in a trial in 1793.\", \"from\": 789, \"to\": 836, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 789, \"end\": 799, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0790180825588203e-31, \"text\": \"Antoinette\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She was famously sentenced to death and beheaded by a guillotine.\", \"from\": 837, \"to\": 902, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is crazy.\", \"from\": 904, \"to\": 918, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Opening your event by replacing Jesus and the disciples at the The Last Supper with men in drag.\", \"from\": 919, \"to\": 1015, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 951, \"end\": 956, \"title\":